  "summary": "Gwendolyn and Gwendraith visit Jackie Avelick to seek information regarding Helen, who fled Dartmouth eighteen years ago. Gwendolyn reveals that they suspect Avelick may have had feelings for Helen. Avelick clarifies that their relationship was merely a youthful flirtation and that he was not brave enough to pursue her seriously. He explains that Helen’s brother, a rigid doctor, prevented them from seeing each other. Avelick admits he visited Helen two or three times in Dartmouth to check on her, but he refuses to help the group further. During the conversation, Avelick reveals he was previously fired from the Fein and Wachman Law Firm due to a setup by an enemy, though he does not name the individual.\n\nAfter the group departs, Gwendraith briefly returns to the house to retrieve a forgotten shawl, witnessing a sharp exchange between Avelick and his wife, Dorothy. As Gwendolyn and Jules drive away, Gwendolyn connects Avelick’s presence to a previous mystery involving a \"mysterious man in a luxury car\" mentioned by Edith Pargette and Lily Kimball. She suspects Avelick was at the scene of a crime on a specific night. Their realization is interrupted when Avelick approaches them from behind a hedge, identifying his eye-catching yellow luxury limousine as \"Little Goldfinch.\"",
